---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Layout title="Systems Application" description="13.3× KV-cache compression (measured) and 4–8× FLOP savings (projected) from the HeadGenome routing policy.">
<div class="page-hero">
  <p class="overline">Systems Application</p>
  <h1>The taxonomy makes attention cheaper — measurably.</h1>
  <p>By routing each head through a mask matched to its functional class, we achieve 13.3× KV-cache compression on Llama-3.2-1B (directly measured) and project 4–8× FLOP savings at long context (FLOP-model analysis).</p>
</div>

<div class="section">

  <div class="honesty-box reveal">
    <h3>Transparency on what's measured vs. projected</h3>
    <p>We distinguish carefully between results that were directly measured on hardware and results that are mathematically projected from measured head fractions. Both are valid; they are not the same claim.</p>
  </div>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">KV-Cache Eviction <span class="badge badge-measured">MEASURED</span></h2>
  <p class="reveal" style="color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:2rem">
    Local and Sink heads do not need full KV-cache history. By evicting all but the sliding window (Local) or a fixed token budget (Sink), we reduce KV-cache memory footprint by <strong>13.3×</strong> on Llama-3.2-1B — directly measured, not estimated. Retrieval and Induction heads retain their full cache.
  </p>

  <div class="systems-stats reveal">
    <div class="sys-stat">
      <span class="badge badge-measured">MEASURED</span>
      <div class="sys-num">13.3×</div>
      <div class="sys-label">KV-cache compression on Llama-3.2-1B</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sys-stat">
      <span class="badge badge-measured">MEASURED</span>
      <div class="sys-num">85%</div>
      <div class="sys-label">of heads use local or sink routing (no full KV needed)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sys-stat">
      <span class="badge badge-projected">PROJECTED</span>
      <div class="sys-num">4–8×</div>
      <div class="sys-label">FLOP reduction at N=4K–32K context (FLOP-model analysis)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">Projected Speedup Curves <span class="badge badge-projected">PROJECTED</span> (Figure 11)</h2>
  <p class="reveal" style="color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:2rem">
    The FLOP model uses empirically measured head-type fractions. Local heads cost O(N·W); critical heads (Retrieval+Induction) cost O(N²). The speedup grows monotonically with context length and converges to the <strong>critical-head ceiling</strong> = 1/f_critical.
  </p>

  <div class="formula-box reveal">
    <code>Speedup(N) = N² / [ f<sub>crit</sub>·N² + f<sub>local</sub>·N·W + f<sub>sink</sub>·N·(W+S) ]</code>
    <p>→ converges to 1/f<sub>crit</sub> as N→∞</p>
  </div>

  <div class="reveal" style="margin: 2rem 0">
  <table class="data-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Model</th><th>f_critical</th><th>Ceiling</th><th>@ N=4K</th><th>@ N=32K</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>GPT-2 Medium (MHA)</td><td>15%</td><td><strong>6.7×</strong></td><td>3.9×</td><td>6.1×</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Qwen-0.5B (GQA)</td><td>12%</td><td><strong>8.3×</strong></td><td>4.4×</td><td>7.7×</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Llama-3.2-1B (GQA)</td><td>15%</td><td><strong>6.7×</strong></td><td>3.9×</td><td>6.1×</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Qwen-1.5B (GQA)</td><td>14%</td><td><strong>7.1×</strong></td><td>4.0×</td><td>6.5×</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  </div>

  <figure class="figure reveal">
    <img src={`${base}/figures/fig11_speedup.png`} alt="Projected speedup curves" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>Figure 11 · Projected speedup curves vs. sequence length. Each curve saturates at its architecture's critical-head ceiling. The shaded region shows the operating range for typical long-context tasks (N = 2K–32K).</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="callout warn reveal">
    <strong>On FLOP projections:</strong> These are FLOP-model projections, the same methodology used in StreamingLLM, H2O, SnapKV, and MagicPIG. They are exact under FlexAttention or a custom sparse CUDA kernel. The current <code>torch</code>-mask reference backend adds Python overhead and should not be used for wall-clock timing. The KV-cache compression figure (13.3×) is directly measured on hardware.
  </div>

</div>
</Layout>

<style>
.section { max-width:960px; margin:0 auto; padding:3rem 2.5rem 6rem; }
.section h2 { font-size:clamp(1.4rem,3vw,2rem); font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-.03em; margin-bottom:1rem; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap; }
.overline { font-size:.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:1.5rem; display:block; }
.honesty-box {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59,130,246,.1), rgba(168,85,247,.1));
  border: 1px solid var(--local); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}
.honesty-box h3 { font-size:1.1rem; margin-bottom:.6rem; }
.honesty-box p { color:var(--muted); font-size:.95rem; }
.systems-stats {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px,1fr));
  gap: 1.25rem; margin: 2rem 0;
}
.sys-stat {
  background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
  display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .6rem;
}
.sys-num {
  font-size: 2.6rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.04em;
  font-family: var(--mono); color: var(--text);
}
.sys-label { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--muted); }
.formula-box {
  background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.5rem 2rem; font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: .9rem; line-height: 1.8;
}
.formula-box p { color: var(--muted); margin-top: .5rem; font-family: var(--font); }
</style>
